                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14167590" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 21:48:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The ascii problem was exactly as the descriptions says, and the changes in AsciiType fix that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When it comes to UTF8, the issue runs deeper.  There ended up being a netty bug (which I will open a ticket for shortly) that caused characters outside of the specified charset to be replaced (by \uFFFD).  Since the native protocol specifies that all strings must be UTF-8, the validation happens in CBUtil.readString().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/thobbs/cassandra-dtest/tree/CASSANDRA-8101&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt; to cover both cases.  In addition to the attached patch, there&apos;s also a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/thobbs/cassandra/tree/CASSANDRA-8101&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;branch&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167608" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 21:59:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pull request for netty opened here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/netty/netty/pull/2999&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/netty/netty/pull/2999&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14168199" author="iamaleksey" created="Sat, 11 Oct 2014 15:13:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM. Nit - imports in CBUtil.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14171316" author="thobbs" created="Tue, 14 Oct 2014 18:24:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like there may be a bug in how unexpected exceptions are handled in 2.1 (in this case, a ProtocolException), but I&apos;ll investigate that and open another ticket if needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
